Referral program design - Retention campaigns - Product ladder expansion - Market expansion strategy - Team scaling plan - Systems and automation - Exit or acquisition prep 9. STRATEGIC PROMPT LIBRARY Create 10 reusable prompts for: 1. Market research synthesis 2. Competitor analysis deep-dive 3. Landing page copy generation 4. Ad creative briefing 5. Email sequence development 6. Webinar script creation 7. Customer objection handling 8. Pricing psychology optimization 9. Launch campaign planning 10. Post-launch analysis and pivot planning Each prompt should include: - Role and context - Specific inputs required - Output format - Citation requirements - Quality checks 10. MONETIZATION & CONVERSION OPTIMIZATION CHECKLIST Create detailed checklists for: - Pre-launch optimization (50+ items) - Launch day protocol (30+ items) - Week 1-4 monitoring (40+ items) - Scaling readiness assessment (35+ items) 11. KNOWLEDGE BASE TEMPLATE STRUCTURE Instructions for maintaining the launch knowledge base with sections for: - Avatar research updates - A/B test results log - Campaign performance archive - Lessons learned journal - Resource and tool library - Competitive intelligence updates 12. APPENDIX: FRAMEWORKS & VISUAL GUIDES Note sections for: - Hook-Story-Offer framework - AIDA and PAS copywriting models - Customer journey mapping template - Funnel visualization guide - Conversion rate optimization hierarchy - Launch checklist master template DESIGN REQUIREMENTS: - Professional business document styling - Clear section headers with numbering - Tables with alternating row colors for readability - Color coding: Blue for strategic, Green for tactical, Orange for optimization, Red for critical alerts - Expandable/collapsible sections - Print-friendly format - Mobile-responsive tables - Action item checkboxes where applicable TONE: Direct, tactical, expert-level strategic guidance. No fluff. Data-backed recommendations. Clear implementation steps suitable for someone who is not a d